		<title>Amish</title>
		<link>http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=676</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 06 Dec 2015 03:36:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Brandyoldfashion]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Miscellaneous]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Faith]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=676</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I had the opportunity to be with Amish for a few hours this past week. I&#8217;ve seen things on TV about them, I&#8217;ve read about them; I&#8217;ve always been curious. They were a father and mother of 6 kids, 4 girls and 2 boys. I really had no expectations, but by the end of the <a class="more-link" href="http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=676">Continue reading <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I had the opportunity to be with Amish for a few hours this past week. I&#8217;ve seen things on TV about them, I&#8217;ve read about them; I&#8217;ve always been curious.<br />
They were a father and mother of 6 kids, 4 girls and 2 boys.<br />
I really had no expectations, but by the end of the couple hours, I would call us friends. He had questions for me, I had questions for them and we spent most of the time just chatting away. We sang a couple hymns that we both knew and they sang one that I didn&#8217;t. I found out that they don&#8217;t waste anything. They&#8217;re not afraid to ask for thing that others would throw out. The mom used to be an Amish school teacher and now their 2 oldest daughters are. He told me that he respects me for not quitting and raising my boys to be well behaved and that I make sure we get to church as much as we can. I told him that I respect him raising his family a step farther away from Satan&#8217;s temptations. He was sure to remind me that Satan is everywhere, and that there are still temptations.<br />
If given the opportunity, I&#8217;d love to spend some more time with them. We may not have the same title on earth, but we&#8217;ll be in Heaven together, and that makes us family in Christ.</p>
<p><a class="a2a_button_facebook" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/facebook?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D676&amp;linkname=Amish" title="Facebook" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_twitter" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/twitter?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D676&amp;linkname=Amish" title="Twitter" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_google_plus" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/google_plus?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D676&amp;linkname=Amish" title="Google+" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_pinterest" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/pinterest?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D676&amp;linkname=Amish" title="Pinterest" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_dd a2a_target addtoany_share_save" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share#url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D676&amp;title=Amish" id="wpa2a_2"></a></p>]]></content:encoded>
