		<title>In a Million Years</title>
		<link>http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=524</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 24 Aug 2015 03:48:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Brandyoldfashion]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[My Faith]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Faith]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Family]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=524</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[In balancing my checkbook tonight preparing to go grocery shopping tomorrow to buy this weeks groceries, I logged onto my bank&#8217;s online site and found that my balance was $0. I didn&#8217;t understand how I could get to exactly $0.00. Before my last transaction, I had $40.34. My last transaction, a trip to Walmart (for <a class="more-link" href="http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=524">Continue reading <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In balancing my checkbook tonight preparing to go grocery shopping tomorrow to buy this weeks groceries, I logged onto my bank&#8217;s online site and found that my balance was $0. I didn&#8217;t understand how I could get to <em>exactly</em> $0.00. Before my last transaction, I had $40.34. My last transaction, a trip to Walmart (for which I have the receipt, since I save my receipts) for 21 items for &#8211; insert drum roll &#8211; $40.34. <em><strong>Exactly</strong></em> $40.34! So on the one hand, it means I won&#8217;t be grocery shopping tomorrow morning, on the other hand, I think I&#8217;m lucky enough to win the lottery. There is no way in a million years I could have planned that. I went into Walmart, picked out 21 items and the cost of them, with tax, equaled the exact amount that I have in my checking account. If it had been even 1 more penny, the debit (or check) would have bounced.<br />
If you know the same God I do, you&#8217;d say that it wasn&#8217;t &#8220;luck.&#8221; Actually, things as crazy as this happen quite a bit around here.</p>
<p><a class="a2a_button_facebook" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/facebook?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D524&amp;linkname=In%20a%20Million%20Years" title="Facebook" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_twitter" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/twitter?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D524&amp;linkname=In%20a%20Million%20Years" title="Twitter" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_google_plus" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/google_plus?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D524&amp;linkname=In%20a%20Million%20Years" title="Google+" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_pinterest" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/pinterest?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D524&amp;linkname=In%20a%20Million%20Years" title="Pinterest" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_dd a2a_target addtoany_share_save" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share#url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D524&amp;title=In%20a%20Million%20Years" id="wpa2a_6"></a></p>]]></content:encoded>
