		<title>Brice</title>
		<link>http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=503</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2015 20:52:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Brandyoldfashion]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Family Dynamic]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[My Faith]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Brice]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Faith]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Family]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=503</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[My bother Brice died on August 5th, 2002. That is a moment that changed my life forever. I would like to think that it changed me for the better despite the actual event itself of losing a brother is one of the most terrible things that can happen to a person and to a family. <a class="more-link" href="http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=503">Continue reading <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My bother Brice died on August 5th, 2002.</p>
<p>That is a moment that changed my life forever. I would like to think that it changed me for the better despite the actual event itself of losing a brother is one of the most terrible things that can happen to a person and to a family. God has taught me many things and my life has slowed down after that day. I make sure that each day my children know that I love them and my priorities for daily life are so different than before that day.</p>
<p>This morning I watched a video of Brice cooking Lobsters. The video is only months before he died. My mom had a company make the DVD from an old video tape. It has a few other clips of family members with Brice in them too.<br />
I was able to watch it without crying. I was able to smile and soak in the video and listen to Brice as he talked. I watched his face; I watched his movements. I remembered my brother. I miss my brother. That fact will never change. And the fact that I don&#8217;t go through a single day without thinking of him in some way will never change either. I still have dreams about him. I still mention him to my boys. I tell them how smart he was and how in some ways that they are like him. But I am at peace that he is gone. I do still cry. I&#8217;m crying as I type this now. Some day I will see him when I get to heaven. He&#8217;ll be waiting for me.Â But for now, it was nice to see him for those few minutes on that video and hear his voice.</p>
<p>I love you Brice and miss you everyday. Tell Grandma and Grandpa Hi. See you when I get there.</p>
