		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=486</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[We&#8217;re on our last roll of toilet paper. Our phones were turned off and I promised the final $68 of the bill would be paid on Friday. Our internet was off and I paid $24 of the back pay to get it turned back on. We got another disconnection notice on our electricity bill for <a class="more-link" href="http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=486">Continue reading <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We&#8217;re on our last roll of toilet paper. Our phones were turned off and I promised the final $68 of the bill would be paid on Friday. Our internet was off and I paid $24 of the back pay to get it turned back on. We got another disconnection notice on our electricity bill for yesterday, so I wrote a bad check for $298.</p>
<p>I have 3 checking accounts: One has 6 cents, One has 25 cents, One has $98.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve sold the old school books on Ebay. I&#8217;ve kept the AC off to lower bills. I don&#8217;t know what else (beside selling my body) I can do to get more money. My parents are at the last of what they can give me and I feel so bad asking for more.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve given it to God. It&#8217;s not in my control. He&#8217;s going have to bail me out because there is no other options. My SSI deposit into my checking account is going to have to come this week. It has to or we will have everything shut off. So it will come because my God is great and He will take care of us.</p>
